# Cursor Rules for CDK-Lib Platform

## MCP Server Configuration
# The Shinobi MCP Server provides platform intelligence capabilities
# It's available at: packages/components/shinobi/mcp-server/dist/index.js

## Available MCP Tools
# - get_component_catalog: Get all platform components
# - get_component_schema: Get component schemas with examples
# - generate_manifest: Generate production-ready manifests
# - get_slo_status: Check service SLO status
# - provision_dashboard: Create monitoring dashboards
# - analyze_change_impact: Analyze deployment impact
# - estimate_cost: Estimate deployment costs
# - check_deployment_readiness: Check deployment readiness

## Available MCP Resources
# - shinobi://components: Component catalog
# - shinobi://services: Service registry
# - shinobi://dependencies: Dependency graph
# - shinobi://compliance: Compliance status

## Usage
# When working with platform components, use the MCP tools to:
# 1. Get component information and schemas
# 2. Generate manifests from descriptions
# 3. Check deployment readiness
# 4. Analyze change impact
# 5. Estimate costs
# 6. Monitor SLO status
